place_info.title: Prayer Room
place_info.address: 成田国際空港 Terminal 2, 1階 1-1 Furugome, Narita, Chiba 282-0004, Japan

reviews.snippet: I would like to sincerely thank the airport for providing this wonderful facility. Having a dedicated prayer room allows Muslim travelers to journey across Tokyo in peace, with the reassurance that their spiritual needs are well accommodated. The prayer room itself is very clean, reflecting the care and respect given to those who use it. Ablution is made easy with taps thoughtfully installed inside the facility, saving time and ensuring convenience. For female travelers, the availability of covers for ablution adds another layer of comfort and dignity. Truly, this facility demonstrates inclusivity and care, making travel in Tokyo even more welcoming.

place_info.address: Japan, 〒282-0004 Chiba, Narita, Furugome, 1-1 成田国際空港 第二旅客ターミナルビル本館 ４階

reviews.snippet:
I had such an enjoyable experience at this café. The food was absolutely delightful — fresh, flavorful, and beautifully presented. Every dish felt thoughtfully prepared, with attention to both taste and detail. The drinks complemented the meal perfectly, making it a truly satisfying dining experience.

The service was equally impressive. The staff were warm, attentive, and genuinely friendly, always ready to help with recommendations and ensuring everything was perfect throughout the visit. Their hospitality made the atmosphere even more welcoming.

The café itself is stylish yet cozy, with a modern interior that balances comfort and elegance. The combination of warm lighting, tasteful décor, and thoughtfully arranged seating creates a relaxed environment where you can enjoy both good food and good company. It’s the kind of place that makes you want to stay longer and return often. Definitely a gem worth visiting!

place_info.title: Hani Capati Kek & Nasi Kukus
place_info.address: NO. 16, JALAN SETIA UTARA 9, BERTAM, BANDAR SETIA FONTAINES, 13200 Kepala Batas, Pulau Pinang, Malaysia

reviews.snippet:
Restoran ini merupakan sebuah kedai makan yang ringkas tetapi mengekalkan tarikan tradisional dengan hidangan-hidangan tempatan yang memuaskan selera. Antara pilihan yang tersedia termasuk roti jala lembut bersama kuah kari pekat, lempeng gulung (kuih ketayap kosong) yang dihidangkan dengan sambal ikan bilis, roti bakar gebu berinti kaya, serta nasi lemak bungkus beraroma daun pisang yang lengkap dengan sambal pedas, ikan bilis rangup, dan telur rebus. Minuman pula merangkumi teh o limau ais yang menyegarkan, teh halia yang wangi, dan teh tarik ais yang kaya rasa.

Suasana kedai sederhana tetapi bersih, sesuai untuk sarapan atau minum petang santai. Hidangan disediakan dengan rasa asli seperti masakan kampung, menjadikannya tempat pilihan bagi mereka yang menggemari sajian tradisional Malaysia. Harga yang berpatutan dan layanan yang mesra menambah lagi daya tarik restoran ini sebagai destinasi menjamu selera yang berbaloi untuk dikunjungi.
reviews.translated_snippet:
This restaurant is a simple eatery that maintains its traditional charm with local dishes that satisfy the taste buds. Among the options available are soft roti jala with thick curry sauce, lepeng gulung (empty ketayap kuih) served with sambal ikan bilis, fluffy roti bakar with a rich filling, and nasi lemak wrapped in banana leaves complete with spicy sambal, crispy ikan bilis, and boiled egg. Drinks include refreshing iced tea o lime, fragrant ginger tea, and richly flavored iced teh tarik.

The atmosphere of the shop is simple but clean, perfect for a leisurely breakfast or afternoon tea. The dishes are prepared with authentic flavors like village cuisine, making it a favorite place for those who love traditional Malaysian dishes. Reasonable prices and friendly service add to the appeal of this restaurant as a dining destination worth visiting.

place_info.title: Bertam Resort & Water Park Penang
place_info.address: PMT 2200, Persiaran Bertam 8, 13200 Kepala Batas, Penang, Malaysia

reviews.snippet:
While Bertam Resort & Water Park boasts impressive architecture and vibrant pools, the overall experience falls short of a true 5-star standard. The themed environment and water park rides are eye-catching, particularly the colorful water slides and aesthetically lit pools at night, as seen in the attached photos. However, the reality behind the visuals presents several disappointments.

Firstly, the buffet dinner was overpriced and did not reflect the quality one would expect from a resort of this class. The food selection was limited and lacked refinement. Additionally, the logistics of moving from the parking area to the main lobby were unnecessarily inconvenient—you have to climb stairs with luggage, which is far from ideal for elderly guests or families with children.

The hot air balloon and themed décor provide photo-worthy moments, but the overall service, planning, and dining experience indicate room for significant improvement. Aesthetic appeal alone is not enough to justify premium pricing.

response.snippet:
Dear Mohd Faiz Hilmi,

Thank you for sharing your detailed feedback on Bertam Resort & Water Park. It is clear that while the resort offers visually appealing attractions and amenities, there are several areas where the experience could be enhanced to meet the expectations. Your observations regarding the dining quality, logistical challenges, and service standards are valuable insights that can guide improvements and will use it to fine-tune our operations so that, upon your next visit, we can bring even more surprises.

Kind Regards,
Navin Nishaal
Executive Assistant Manager

place_info.title: The Campus Ampang
place_info.address: Lot 7706, Jalan Kolam Air Lama, Mukim, Hulu Kelang, 68000 Ampang, Selangor, Malaysia

reviews.snippet: The Campus Ampang, though often praised for its adaptive reuse of the former ISKL grounds, feels somewhat overhyped upon closer experience. While the preservation of original architecture and integration of natural elements is commendable, the space leans more on aesthetic nostalgia than practical appeal. Despite housing over 80 outlets, including trendy names like Qra and Universal Bakehouse, the tenant mix lacks cohesion and novelty, with many offerings resembling what’s already available in more accessible malls around KL. The layout, though airy, can feel disjointed, and the emphasis on being a “community hub” seems more aspirational than actual. For visitors expecting a groundbreaking urban experience, The Campus may come off as style over substance.

place_info.title: Oriental Kopi
place_info.address: Lot 170-B1-45, Plaza Gurney, 46, Persiaran Gurney, 10250 George Town, Pulau Pinang, Malaysia

reviews.snippet:
Oriental Kopi offers a nostalgic yet elevated kopitiam experience with a menu that pays homage to traditional Malaysian flavors, beautifully presented and satisfying to the palate. The toast—crispy, golden-brown on the outside—offers a comforting start, likely filled with kaya and butter, true to classic kopitiam roots. The noodle bowl presents a well-balanced composition of textures and ingredients: soft-boiled egg, shredded chicken, fried shallots, vegetables, and tofu skin, echoing a refined version of a local dry noodle specialty.

The refreshing herbal drink, infused with longan, red dates, goji berries, and chrysanthemum, is not only visually appealing but also offers a soothing counterpoint to the richer dishes. The shrimp fried rice is aromatic and fluffy, garnished with scallions and cucumber slices—simple, hearty, and satisfying. Meanwhile, the prawn noodles are robust, rich in umami, and generously topped with prawns, shredded chicken, and boiled egg, delivering the depth of a traditional Penang-style Hokkien Mee.

To end on a sweet note, the egg tarts are a highlight—flaky pastry with glossy, custard-like filling, delicately caramelized on top. Paired with the iconic frothy iced kopi, the meal encapsulates the essence of a classic yet contemporary Malaysian dining affair. Overall, Oriental Kopi succeeds in combining authenticity with quality, making it a worthy destination for both locals and visitors seeking comfort food with finesse.

place_info.title: Dolly Dim Sum, Sunway Carnival Mall
place_info.address: LG-26 and LG-27 Sunway Carnival Mall 3068 Jalan Todak Pusat Bandar Seberang Jaya Seberang Jaya, 13700 Perai, Pulau Pinang, Malaysia

reviews.snippet: At Dolly Dim Sum in Sunway Carnival Mall, Seberang Jaya, diners can expect a pleasant and satisfying dining experience. One of the standout dishes is the *Crispy Egg Noodles*, served with a generous topping of tender sliced chicken, fresh vegetables including napa cabbage, carrots, snow peas, and mushrooms, all coated in a flavorful, glossy gravy. The noodles start off with a satisfying crunch, gradually softening as they soak up the sauce, creating a delightful contrast in texture. For dessert or a sweet treat, the *Egg Custard Bun* comes highly recommended. Steamed to perfection, the soft bun reveals a rich, molten custard filling that flows out with each bite—sweet, creamy, and indulgent. It's a must-try item that perfectly complements the savory mains and rounds off the meal beautifully.
